        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 4 at 6:28PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles east of Cannon Ball, or 11 miles northwest of Linton. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Linton, Strasburg, Hague, Westfield, Temvik, Cattail Recreation Area,
Beaver Bay Recreation Area, and Hull.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding.</instruction>
